gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Nuggets 124, Lakers 114
gameRecap.excerpt: Denver wins their 6th game in a row as they defeat Los Angeles, 124-114. For Denver, Nikola Jokic led the way with 35 points, 10 rebounds, and seven assists aided by Michael Porter Jr. (25 points (five 3PM), 10 rebounds, four assists) and Jamal Murray (24 points, six rebounds, and 11 assists) in the victory. Lebron James recorded 26 points, nine assists, and three steals with Rui Hachimura tallying 23 points and Austin Reaves putting up 19 points and 14 assists for Los Angeles in the losing effort. Denver improves to 42-19 on the season, while Los Angeles moves to 33-29 with the loss.
